        <profileDesc>
            <creation/>
            <abstract>
                <p>Magic prayer to bind various demons or magicians. <foreign xml:lang="gez">Lebā māš</foreign> may be related to 
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">Lobā</foreign>, which is a name for Satan or to 
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">Lebāb</foreign>, which is transcribed from the Arabic term <foreign xml:lang="ar">lubāb</foreign> 
                    meaning "the better one", both of which are mentioned in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/P56A9HHG"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1955Prieres"/><title level="m">Prières magiques éthiopiennes pour délier les charmes (&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;maftǝḥe šǝrāy&lt;/hi&gt;)</title><title level="s">&lt;Rocznik orientalistyczny&gt;</title><author><forename>Stefan</forename><surname>Strelcyn</surname></author><pubPlace>Warszawa</pubPlace><publisher>Państwowe wydawnictwo naukowe</publisher><date>1955</date><series><title level="s">&lt;Rocznik orientalistyczny&gt;</title><biblScope unit="volume">18</biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">18</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Strelcyn1955Prieres</note><note type="tag">Magic scrols</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Strelcyn1955Prieres</note><note type="tag">Magic scrols</note><citedRange unit="page">416</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">Qamañā</foreign> is mentioned as a wizard in 
                    <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/P56A9HHG"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1955Prieres"/><title level="m">Prières magiques éthiopiennes pour délier les charmes (&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;maftǝḥe šǝrāy&lt;/hi&gt;)</title><title level="s">&lt;Rocznik orientalistyczny&gt;</title><author><forename>Stefan</forename><surname>Strelcyn</surname></author><pubPlace>Warszawa</pubPlace><publisher>Państwowe wydawnictwo naukowe</publisher><date>1955</date><series><title level="s">&lt;Rocznik orientalistyczny&gt;</title><biblScope unit="volume">18</biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">18</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Strelcyn1955Prieres</note><note type="tag">Magic scrols</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Strelcyn1955Prieres</note><note type="tag">Magic scrols</note><citedRange unit="page">435</citedRange></bibl>.
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾAbenezer</foreign>" is perhaps related to the ancient location Eben-Ezer in Judea, which was 
                    mentioned in the Hebrew version of <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2697Sam">1 Reg 4:1</ref> (probably
                    also related to <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾAbunāzǝr</foreign>, which was mentioned in 
                    <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/P56A9HHG"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1955Prieres"/><title level="m">Prières magiques éthiopiennes pour délier les charmes (&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;maftǝḥe šǝrāy&lt;/hi&gt;)</title><title level="s">&lt;Rocznik orientalistyczny&gt;</title><author><forename>Stefan</forename><surname>Strelcyn</surname></author><pubPlace>Warszawa</pubPlace><publisher>Państwowe wydawnictwo naukowe</publisher><date>1955</date><series><title level="s">&lt;Rocznik orientalistyczny&gt;</title><biblScope unit="volume">18</biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">18</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Strelcyn1955Prieres</note><note type="tag">Magic scrols</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Strelcyn1955Prieres</note><note type="tag">Magic scrols</note><citedRange unit="page">452 </citedRange></bibl>, but with another 
                    explanation). Partly written with Amharic terms and irregular orthography.</p>
            </abstract>
